  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UN-OCHA/Yemen ERF, 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The nutrition situation has for decades been critical in Yemen. According to the UN Children&apos;s Fund (UNICEF) almost half the country&apos;s children are chronically malnourished, which is one of the highest proportions globally. The number of acutely malnourished children has decreased from 1 million to 840,000 over the last year, primarily due to humanitarian efforts as well as improved access to data.

In the overall response is the UN&apos;s Central Emergency Response Fund (ERF) a key instrument because it is used for rapid and flexible funding on areas which is prioritized by the UN humanitarian country team under the leadership of the Humanitarian Coordinator.</narrative>
  </description>
